def: In the manner or form of an ecclesiastical chapter. Sterne.
Having a nauseous odor; fetid; poisonous. [R.]
Work done as a task; also, work done by the job; piecework.
A combining form denoting relation to the throat; as, gutturo-nasal, having both a guttural and a nasal character; gutturo-palatal.
A student of, or one versed in, epigraphy.
A small, edible, freshwater European perch (Aspro zingel),having a round, elongated body and prominent snout.
The positive pole of an electric battery, or more strictly theelectrode by which the current enters the electrolyte on its way tothe other pole; -- opposed to cathode.
